<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">
<step><![CDATA[Pre-heat the oven to 180C/gas mark 5.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[To make the dropped scones, sieve the flour and baking powder into a bowl, and then add the sugar. Stir in the golden syrup, eggs and enough of the milk to form a thick smooth batter that just drops off the spoon.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Heat a griddle pan, girdle or non-stick frying pan and rub it with a little butter. Drop spoonfuls of the mixture into the pan and let them cook for 3 minutes until bubbles rise, then turn them over with a palette knife or spatula and cook for another 2-3 minutes. Place them on kitchen paper while you are cooking the rest.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Serve warm with the cherries scattered over and a spoonful of yoghurt or crÃ¨me fraÃ®che, finished with a drizzle of clear honey.]]></step>
